\title{Monoid}
\taxon{Definition}
\p{
A set #{S} equipped with a binary operation #{S\times S\to S}, which we will denote #{\circ}, is a \strong{monoid} if it satisfies the following two axioms:
\ul{
\li{Associativity: #{\forall a,b,c\in S, (a\circ b) \circ c= a \circ (b \circ c)}}
\li{Identity: #{\exists e\in S} such that #{\forall g\in S, g\circ e=e\circ g = g}}
}
}